 leaders and organizations. Forman and Ross propose an emerging Integral perspective and suggest integral modes of performance management, change management, and teamwork. Ultimately, the Integral perspective gives leaders the insight and flexibility to use a range of resources to meet organizational needs in a rapidly changing world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aLeadership. 4aBusiness and Economics : Business Administration. 4aBusiness and Economics : Organization Theory. 4aPolitics and Law : Leadership Studies. 4aPsychology : Integral Theory. 4aPsychology : Transpersonal Psychology. 7aPSYCHOLOGY / Movements / Transpersonal.2bisacsh1 aRoss, Laurel A., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438446288423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438446288/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles